# MindReply Development Standards

## Core Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS
- React 18.3+

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., HeroSection.tsx)
- Functions: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Types: PascalCase (e.g., User, Professional)

## Folder Structure
```
app/              - Next.js App Router pages
components/       - Reusable React components
lib/              - Utilities and helpers
types/            - TypeScript definitions
public/           - Static assets
messages/         - i18n translations (8+ languages)
azure/            - Azure integration blueprints
datadog/          - Monitoring configuration
```

## No-Spend Policy
- DO NOT create test subscriptions without approval
- DO NOT use paid AI services in development
- Use free tier providers (e.g., free Stripe test keys)
- All integrations must have free fallbacks

## Color Scheme (MindReply Brand)
- Navy: #0A1628
- Gold: #C9A961
- Cream: #F8F5F0
- Accent: #1E3A5F

## Component Patterns
- Use 'use client' for interactive components
- Props should be typed with interfaces
- All API calls through lib/api.ts
- State management with zustand

## Azure Integration Requirements
- Function App blueprints in /azure folder
- Logic App workflow definitions
- Event Grid topic configuration
- NO actual deployment without approval

## Datadog Monitoring
- Define metrics in /datadog folder
- Error rate checks required
- API latency monitoring
- Custom dashboard definitions

## Multilingual Support
- 8 languages: EN, BG, DE, FR, ES, IT, PT, JA
- Use next-intl library
- All UI strings in messages/ folder
- Language switcher component required

## TypeScript Requirements
- No 'any' types
- Strict mode: true
- All exports must be typed
- Use union types for variants

## Performance
- Image optimization required
- Code splitting for routes
- SWR/React Query for data fetching
- Lazy load heavy components

## Security
- All API keys in .env.local (git-ignored)
- No hardcoded credentials
- CORS headers on API routes
- Rate limiting on endpoints

## Testing
- Jest configuration required
- Component tests for features
- E2E tests for critical flows
- Minimum 80% coverage

## Git Workflow
- Feature branches: feature/description
- Commit messages: type: description
- No direct pushes to main
- Require PR reviews

## Deployment
- Vercel auto-deploys from main
- Environment variables via Vercel dashboard
- Preview environments for PRs
- Production monitoring enabled
